EngDesc.value: This threat represents a file being downloaded with an unknown extension, but contains CLSID which invokes the Microsoft HTML Application host scripting. This allows an attacker to represent a file with a bogus extension and mime-type which can be executed by the host downloading the application. For instance, sending an file with the extension of d0c and mime type of application/msword, but with the CLSID of MSHTA. This threat is a client attack that comes from the virtual server.
